@startuml

title Site Administration Extended Control Sequence Diagram

actor "Site Admin" as Admin

participant "Frontend (Web Portal)" as FE
participant "Apache\n(HTTP Server)" as Apache

box "Laravel Application" #LightGreen
  participant "Middleware" as MW
  participant "Controller" as C
  participant "Site Administration Service" as Service
  participant "Eloquent ORM" as ORM
end box

database "MariaDB Database" as DB

note right of Admin
Site Admin has full system privileges.
They can perform all actions available to:
- Inventory Admin
- Marketplace Admin
- Facility Admin
Those workflows are not repeated here.
end note


== Assign / Update / Remove User Role ==
Admin -> FE: Search user and assign/update/remove role
activate Admin
activate FE

FE -> Apache: POST /admin/updateUserRole
activate Apache
Apache -> MW: Forward request
deactivate Apache

activate MW
MW -> C: Pass validated request
deactivate MW

activate C
C -> Service: updateUserRole(userId, role)
activate Service

Service -> ORM: Query user
activate ORM
ORM -> DB: Select user record
activate DB
DB --> ORM: User found
deactivate DB
ORM --> Service: User entity
deactivate ORM

Service -> ORM: Update role assignment
activate ORM
ORM -> DB: Update user role
activate DB
DB --> ORM: Role updated
deactivate DB
ORM --> Service: Role persisted
deactivate ORM

Service --> C: Role update confirmed
deactivate Service
C --> FE: Display confirmation
deactivate C

FE --> Admin: Show "User role updated"
deactivate FE
deactivate Admin


== Modify Facility Cost Equation ==
Admin -> FE: Update cost report formula
activate Admin
activate FE

FE -> Apache: POST /admin/updateCostFormula
activate Apache
Apache -> MW: Forward request
deactivate Apache

activate MW
MW -> C: Pass validated request
deactivate MW

activate C
C -> Service: updateCostFormula(newEquation)
activate Service

Service -> ORM: Store new formula
activate ORM
ORM -> DB: Update formula configuration
activate DB
DB --> ORM: Formula saved
deactivate DB
ORM --> Service: Formula persisted
deactivate ORM

Service --> C: Update confirmed
deactivate Service
C --> FE: Display confirmation
deactivate C

FE --> Admin: Show "Facility cost equation updated"
deactivate FE
deactivate Admin

@enduml